    "code": "012", 
    "data": "The Supererogatory Dawn Prayer\nUpon accomplishment of the Night Prayer, you may stand up for offering the supererogatory dawn prayer, which consists of two units in the first of which you may recite Surah al-Faatehah and Surah al-Kafirun and in the second unit Surah al-Faatehah and Surah al-Tawheed. When you accomplish the prayer, you may sleep on the right side like a dead in the grave, put your right cheek on your right hand, and say the following:\nاِسْتَمْسَكْتُ بِعُرْوَةِ اللهِ الْوُثْقَى\nISTAMSAKTO BE-U’RWATIL WUSQAL\nI have laid hold on Allah’s firmest handle\nالَّتِي لَا انْفِصَامَ لَهَا\nLATEE LAN FE-SAAMA LAHAA\nthat shall never break off.\nوَ اعْتَصَمْتُ بِحَبْلِ اللهِ الْمَتِيْنِ\nWA’ TASAMTO BE-HABLIL LAAHIL MATEENE\nI have held fast to Allah’s solid rope.\nوَ اَعُوذُ بِاللهِ مِنْ شَرِّ فَسَقَةِ الْعَرَبِ وَ الْعَجَمِ\nWA A-O’OZO BILLAAHE MIN SHARRE FASAQATIL A’RABE WAL A’JAME\nI pray for Allah’s protection against the evil of the sinful Arabs and non-Arabs.\nوَ اَعُوذُ بِاللهِ مِنْ شَرِّ فَسَقَةِ الْجِنِّ وَ الْاِنْسِ\nWA A-O’OZO BILLAAHE MIN SHARRE FASAQATIL JINNE WAL INSE.\nI pray for Allah’s protection against the evil of the sinful jinn and men.\nYou may then repeat the following doxology three times:\nسُبْحَانَ رَبِّ الصَّبَاحِ فَالِقِ الاِصْبَاحِ\nSUBHAANA RABBIS SABAAHE FAALEQIL ISBAAHE\nAll glory be to the Lord of mornings, the Cleaver of daybreak.\nYou may then recite the previously mentioned five verses of Surah Al-’Imran.\nYou may then sit and say Tasbih al-Zahra’.\nIn the book of Man-La-Yahduruhul-Faqih, it is reported that whoever invoke blessings upon the Holy Prophet and his Household one hundred times between the supererogatory and the obligatory dawn prayers, Almighty Allah will save his face from the heat of Hellfire:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَآلِ مُحَمَّدٍ\nALLAAHUMMA SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN.\nO Allah, (please) send blessings upon Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad,\nWhoever repeats the following supplicatory prayer one hundred times, Almighty Allah will build for him a house in Paradise:\nسُبْحَانَ رَبِّيَ الْعَظِيْمِ وَ بِحَمْدِهٖ\nSUBHAANA RABBEYAL A’ZEEME WA BEHAMDEHI\nAll glory be to my Lord, the All-great, and in praise of Him.\nاَسْتَغْفِرُ اللهَ رَبِّي وَ اَتُوبُ اِلَيْهِ\nASTAGHFERUL LAAHE RABBEE WA ATOOBO ELAYHE.\nI implore Allah, my Lord, for forgiveness and I repent to Him.\nWhoever recites Surah al-Tawheed twenty-one times, Almighty Allah will build for him a house in Paradise, and whoever recites it forty times, Almighty Allah will forgive him.\nAfter accomplishing the Night Prayer, it is highly advisable to say the thirty-second supplication of al-Sahifah al-Kamilah al-Sajjadiyyah:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ يَا ذَا الْمُلْكِ الْمُتَاَبِّدِ بِالْخُلُودِ…\nALLAAHUMMA YAA ZAL MULKIL MOTA-ABBEDE BIL-KHOLOODE.\nO Allah, O Possessor of kingdom perpetual in everlastingness… \nYou may then do a thanksgiving prostration during which you are highly advised to pray for the good of your brothers-in-faith and say the aforementioned supplication that is said in the thanksgiving prostrations:\nاَللّٰهُمَّ رَبَّ الْفَجْرِ وَاللَّيَالِي الْعَشْرِ\nALLAAHUMMA RABBAL FAJRE WAL LAYAALIL A’SHRE\nO Allah, O Lord of the daybreak, the ten nights,\nوَ الشَّفْعِ وَ الْوَتْرِ\nWASH SHAF-E’ WAL WATRE\nthe even and the odd,\nوَ اللَّيْلِ اِذَا يَسْرِ\nWAL LAYLE EZAA YASRE\nand the night when it departs!\nوَ رَبَّ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ\nWA RABBA KULLE SHAY-IN\nO Lord of all things!\nوَ اِلٰهَ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ\nWA ELAAHA KULLE SHAY-IN\nO Lord of all things!\nوَ خَالِقَ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ\nWA KHAALEQA KULLE SHAY-IN\nO Creator of all things!\nوَ مَلِكَ كُلِّ شَيْءٍ\nWA MALEKA KULLE SHAY-IN\nO King of all things!\nصَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ آلِهٖ\nSALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADINW WA AALEHI\n(Please) send blessings upon Muhammad and his Household,\nوَ افْعَلْ بِي وَ بِـ… مَا اَنْتَ اَهْلُهٗ\nWAF A’L BEE WA BE… MAA ANTA AHLOHU\ndo to me and to so-and-so that which befits You,\nوَ لَا تَفْعَلْ بِنَا مَا نَحْنُ اَهْلُهٗ\nWA LAA TAF-A’L BENAA MAA NAHNO AHLOHU\nbut do not do to us that which we deserve,\nفَاِنَّكَ اَهْلُ التَّقْوٰى وَ اَهْلُ الْمَغْفِرَةِ\nFA-INNAKA AHLUT TAQWAA WA AHLUL MAGHFERATE.\nfor You are verily worthy to be feared and worthy to forgive.\nI please my faithful brothers to mention me - the sinful whose face has been blackened by sins - in their supplications, because I am in urgent need for prayers. Eventually, Allah is the source of success.", 
    "title": "Nafilah Fajr"
}